  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>School</strong>&nbsp;illusion&nbsp;(glamer);\n    <strong>Level</strong>&nbsp;bard 3, hunter 3, ranger 3, sorcerer/wizard 3;\n    \n    \n    \n    \n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Casting Time</strong>&nbsp;1 standard action<br>\n    <strong>Components</strong>&nbsp;V, S<br>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Range</strong>&nbsp;touch<br>\n    \n    <strong>Targets</strong>&nbsp;creature touched<br>\n    \n    <strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;1 round/level<br>\n    <strong>Saving Throw</strong>&nbsp;Will negates (harmless);&nbsp;<strong>Spell Resistance</strong>&nbsp;yes<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  <p>A touched creature becomes invisible (as per invisibility) as long as it is in direct sunlight (or bright light shed by a <i>daylight</i> spell). If an action the target creature takes causes the invisible creature to become visible but does not end the <i>sunstalker</i> spell's duration, the creature can use this spell's magic to become invisible again as a standard action as long as it stands in an area of sunlight (as defined above). The creature gains only concealment (20% miss chance) in normal light.</p>\n</div>\n",
